using System;  // Namespace declaration

namespace MyFirstApp   // Namespace
{
    class Program      // Class
    {
        static void Main(string[] args)   // Entry point
        {
            Console.WriteLine("Hello, World!"); // Statement
        }
    }
}

Key point

1.using System; → imports libraries (System has Console).

2.namespace → logical grouping of classes.

3.class Program → C# programs are inside classes.

4.Main method → starting point of every C# program.

Console.WriteLine() → outputs text to the screen.
